obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (30092)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30092&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the ^1*** Sale of Goods Act,`
  line 1930.
  line
  line `^2[(2) It extends to the whole of India ^3***.]`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on the 1st day of July, 1930.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "Indian" omitted by Act 33 of 1963, s. 2 (w.e.f. 22-9-1963).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `3. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (30093)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 1993, s. 31 and the Schedule, Part III.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30093&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,—`
  line
  line `(1) "buyer" means a person who buys or agrees to buy goods;`
  line
  line `(2) "delivery" means voluntary transfer of possession from one person to another;`
  line
  line `(3) goods are said to be in a "deliverable state" when they are in such state that the buyer would`
  line `under the contract be bound to take delivery of them;`
  line
  line `(4) "document of title to goods" includes a bill of lading, dockwarrant, warehouse keeper's`
  line `certificate, wharfingers' certificate, railway receipt, ^1[multimodal transport document, ] warrant or`
  line `order for the delivery of goods and any other document used in the ordinary course of business as`
  line `proof of the possession or control of goods, or authorising or purporting to authorise, either by`
  line `endorsement or by delivery, the possessor of the document to transfer or receive goods thereby`
  line represented;
  line
  line `(5) "fault" means wrongful act or default;`
  line
  line `(6) "future goods" means goods to be manufactured or produced or acquired by the seller after the`
  line `making of the contract of sale;`
  line
  line `(7) "goods" means every kind of moveable property other than actionable claims and money; and`
  line `includes stock and shares, growing crops, grass, and things attached to or forming part of the land`
  line `which are agreed to be severed before sale or under the contract of sale;`
  line
  line `(8) a person is said to be "insolvent" who has ceased to pay his debts in the ordinary course of`
  line `business, or cannot pay his debts as they become due, whether he has committed an act of insolvency`
  line `or not;`
  line
  line `(9) "mercantile agent" means a mercantile agent having in the customary course of business as`
  line `such agent authority either to sell goods, or to consign goods for the purposes of sale, or to buy goods,`
  line `or to raise money on the security of goods;`
  line
  line `(10) "price" means the money consideration for a sale of goods;`
  line
  line `(11) "property" means the general property in goods, and not merely a special property;`
  line
  line `(12) "quality of goods" includes their state or condition;`
  line
  line `(13) "seller" means a person who sells or agrees to sell goods;`
  line
  line `(14) "specific goods" means goods identified and agreed upon at the time a contract of sale is`
  line `made; and`
  line
  line `(15) expressions used but not defined in this Act and defined in the Indian Contract Act, 1872`
  line `(9 of 1872), have the meaning assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (30094)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Application of provisions of Act 9 of 1872.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30094&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The unrepealed provisions of the Indian Contract`
  line `Act, 1872, save in so far as they are inconsistent with the express provisions of this Act, shall continue to`
  line `apply to contracts for the sale of goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (30095)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Sale and agreement to sell.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30095&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) A contract of sale of goods is a contract whereby the seller`
  line `transfers or agrees to transfer the property in goods to the buyer for a price. There may be a contract of`
  line `sale between one part-owner and another.`
  line
  line `(2) A contract of sale may be absolute or conditional.`
  line
  line `(3) Where under a contract of sale the property in the goods is transferred from the seller to the buyer,`
  line `the contract is called a sale, but where the transfer of the property in the goods is to take place at a future`
  line `time or subject to some condition thereafter to be fulfilled, the contract is called an agreement to sell.`
  line
  line `(4) An agreement to, sell becomes a sale when the time elapses or the conditions are fulfilled subject`
  line `to which the property in the goods is to be transferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (30096)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Contract of sale how made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30096&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) A contract of sale is made by an offer to buy or sell goods for a`
  line `price and the acceptance of such offer. The contract may provide for the immediate delivery of the goods`
  line `or immediate payment of the price or both, or for the delivery or payment by instalments, or that the`
  line `delivery or payment or both shall be postponed.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of any law for the time being in force, a contract of sale may be made in`
  line `writing or by word of mouth, or partly in writing and partly by word of mouth or may be implied from the`
  line `conduct of the parties.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (30097)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Existing or future goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30097&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The goods which form the subject of a contract of sale may be`
  line `either existing goods, owned or possessed by the seller, or future goods.`
  line
  line `(2) There may be a contract for the sale of goods the acquisition of which by the seller depends upon`
  line `a contingency which may or may not happen.`
  line
  line `(3) Where by a contract of sale the seller purports to effect a present sale of future goods, the contract`
  line `operates as an agreement to sell the goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (30098)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Goods perishing before making of contract.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30098&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Where there is a contract for the sale of specific`
  line `goods, the contract is void if the goods without the knowledge of the seller have, at the time when the`
  line `contract was made, perished or become so damaged as no longer to answer to their description in the`
  line contract.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (30099)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Goods perishing before sale but after agreement to sell.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30099&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Where there is an agreement to sell`
  line `specific goods, and subsequently the goods without any fault on the part of the seller or buyer perish or`
  line `become so damaged as no longer to answer to their description in the agreement before the risk passes to`
  line `the buyer, the agreement is thereby avoided.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (30100)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Ascertainment of price.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30100&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The price in a contract of sale may be fixed by the contract or may`
  line `be left to be fixed in manner thereby agreed or may be determined by the course of dealing between the`
  line parties.
  line
  line `(2) Where the price is not determined in accordance with the foregoing provisions, the buyer shall`
  line `pay the seller a reasonable price. What is a reasonable price is a question of fact dependent on the`
  line `circumstances of each particular case.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (30101)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Agreement to sell at valuation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30101&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where there is an agreement to sell goods on the terms that`
  line `the price is to be fixed by the valuation of a third party and such third party cannot or does not make such`
  line `valuation, the agreement is thereby avoided:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the goods or any part thereof have been delivered to, and appropriated by, the buyer,`
  line `he shall pay a reasonable price therefor.`
  line
  line `(2) Where such third party is prevented from making the valuation by the fault of the seller or buyer,`
  line `the party not in fault may maintain a suit for damages against the party in fault`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (30102)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Stipulations as to time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30102&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Unless a different intention appears from the terms of the contract,`
  line `stipulations as to time of payment arc not deemed to be of the essence of a contract of sale. Whether any`
  line `other Stipulation as to time is of the essence of the contract or not depends on the terms of the contract.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (30103)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Condition and warranty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30103&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) A stipulation in a contract of sale with reference to goods which`
  line `are the subject thereof may be a condition or a warranty.`
  line
  line `(2) A condition is a stipulation essential to the main purpose of the contract, the breach of which`
  line `gives rise to a right to treat the contract as repudiated.`
  line
  line `(3) A warranty is a stipulation collateral to the main purpose of the contract, the breach of which`
  line `gives rise to a claim for damages but not to a right to reject the goods and treat the contract as repudiated.`
  line
  line `(4) Whether a stipulation in a contract of sale is a condition or a warranty depends in each case on the`
  line `construction of the contract. A stipulation may be a condition, though called a warranty in the contract.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (30104)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `When condition to be treated as warranty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30104&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a contract of sale is subject to any`
  line `condition to be fulfilled by the seller, the buyer may waive the condition or elect to treat`
  line `the breach of the condition as a breach of warranty and not as a ground for treating the contract as`
  line repudiated.
  line
  line `(2) Where a contract of sale is not severable and the buyer has accepted the goods or part thereof,`
  line `^1*** the breach of any condition to be fulfilled by the seller can only be treated as a breach of warranty`
  line `and not as a ground for rejecting the goods and treating the contract as .repudiated, unless there is a term`
  line `of the contract, express or implied, to that effect.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall affect the case of any condition or warranty fulfilment of which is`
  line `excused by law by reason of impossibility or otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "or where the contract is for specific goods the property in which has passed to the buyer," omitted by Act 33 of`
  line `1963, s. 3 (w.e.f. 22-9-1963).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (30105)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Implied undertaking as to title, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30105&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `In a contract of sale, unless the circumstances of the`
  line `contract are such as to show a different intention, there is—`
  line
  line `(a) an implied condition on the part of the seller that, in the case of a sale, he has a right to sell the`
  line `goods and that, in the case of an agreement to sell, he will have a right to sell the goods at the time`
  line `when the property is to pass;`
  line
  line `(b) an implied warranty that the buyer shall have and enjoy quiet possession of the goods;`
  line
  line `(c) an implied warranty that the goods shall be free from any charge or encumbrance in favour of`
  line `any third party not declared or known to the buyer before or at the time when the contract is made.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (30106)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Sale by description.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30106&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Where there is a contract for the sale of goods by description, there is an`
  line `implied condition that the goods shall correspond with the description; and, if the sale is by sample as`
  line `well as by description, it is not sufficient that the bulk of the goods corresponds with the sample if the`
  line `goods do not also correspond with the description.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (30107)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Implied conditions as to quality or fitness.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30107&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act and of any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, there is no implied warranty or condition as to the quality or fitness`
  line `for any particular purpose of goods supplied under a contract of sale, except as follows:—`
  line
  line `(1) Where the buyer, expressly or by implication, makes known to the seller the particular`
  line `purpose for which the goods are required, so as to show that the buyer relies on the seller's skill or`
  line `judgment, and the goods are of a description which it is in the course of the sellers business to supply`
  line `(whether he is the manufacturer or producer or not), there is an implied condition that the goods shall`
  line `be reasonably fit for such purpose:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in the case of a contract for the sale of a specified article under its patent or other`
  line `trade name, there is no implied condition as to its fitness for any particular purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) Where goods are bought by description from a seller who deals in goods of that description`
  line `(whether he is the manufacturer or producer or not), there is an implied condition that the goods shall`
  line `be of merchantable quality:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the buyer has examined the goods, there shall be no implied condition as regards`
  line `defects which such examination ought to have revealed.`
  line
  line `(3) An implied warranty or condition as to quality or fitness for a particular purpose may be`
  line `annexed by the usage of trade.`
  line
  line `(4) An express warranty or condition does not negative a warranty or condition implied by this`
  line `Act unless inconsistent therewith.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (30108)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Sale by sample.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30108&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) A contract of sale is a contract for sale by sample where there is a term in`
  line `the contract, express or implied, to that effect.`
  line
  line `(2) In the case of a contract for sale by sample there is an implied condition—`
  line
  line `(a) that the bulk shall correspond with the sample in quality;`
  line
  line `(b) that the buyer shall have a reasonable opportunity of comparing the bulk with the sample;`
  line
  line `(c) that the goods shall be free from any defect, rendering them unmerchantable, which would not`
  line `be apparent on reasonable examination of the sample.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (30109)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Goods must be ascertained.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30109&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Where there is a contract for the sale of unascertained goods, no`
  line `property in the goods is transferred to the buyer unless and until the goods are ascertained.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (30110)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Property passes when intended to pass.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30110&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where there is a contract for the sale of specific`
  line `or ascertained goods the property in them is transferred to the buyer at such time as the parties to the`
  line `contract intend it to he transferred.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of ascertaining the intention of the parties regard shall be had to the terms of the`
  line `contract, the conduct of the parties and the circumstances of the case.`
  line
  line `(3) Unless a different intention appears, the rules contained in sections 20 to 24 are rules for`
  line `ascertaining the intention of the parties as to the time at which the property in the goods is to pass to the`
  line buyer.
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (30111)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Specific goods in a deliverable state.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30111&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Where there is an unconditional contract for the sale of`
  line `specific goods in a deliverable state, the property in the goods passes to the buyer when the contract is`
  line `made, and it is immaterial whether the time of payment of the price or the time of delivery of the goods,`
  line `or both, is postponed.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (30112)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Specific goods to be put into a deliverable state.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30112&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Where there is a contract for the sale of`
  line `specific goods and the seller is bound to do something to the goods for the purpose of putting them into a`
  line `deliverable state, the property does not pass until such thing is done and the buyer has notice thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (30113)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Specific goods in a deliverable state, when the seller has to do anything thereto in order to ascertain price.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30113&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Where there is a contract for the sale of specific goods in a deliverable state, but the`
  line `seller is bound to weigh, measure, test or do some other act or thing with reference to the goods for the`
  line `purpose of ascertaining the price, the property does not pass until such act or thing is done and the buyer`
  line `has notice thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (30114)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Sale of unascertained goods and appropriation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30114&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where there is a contract for the sale of`
  line `unascertained or future goods by description and goods of that description and in a deliverable state are`
  line `unconditionally appropriated to the contract, either by the seller with the assent of the buyer or by the`
  line `buyer with the assent of the seller, the property in the goods thereupon passes to the buyer. Such assent`
  line `may be express or implied, and may by given either before or after the appropriation is made.`
  line
  line `Delivery to carrier.—(2) Where, in pursuance of the contract, the seller delivers the goods to the`
  line `buyer or to a carrier or other bailee (whether named by the buyer or not) for the purpose of transmission`
  line `to the buyer, and does not reserve the right of disposal, he is deemed to have unconditionally appropriated`
  line `the goods to the contract.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (30115)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Goods sent on approval or “on sale or return”.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30115&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `When goods are delivered to the buyer on`
  line `approval or "on sale or return" or other similar terms, the property therein passes to the buyer`
  line
  line `(a) when he signifies his approval or acceptance to the seller or does any other act adopting the`
  line transaction;
  line
  line `(b) if he does not signify his approval or acceptance to the seller but retains the goods without`
  line `giving notice of rejection, then, if a time has been fixed for the return of the goods, on the expiration`
  line `of such time, and, if no time has been fixed, on the expiration of a reasonable time.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (30116)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Reservation of right of disposal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Subs by Act 33 of 1963, s. 4, for sub-sections (2) and (3) (w.e.f. 22-9-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30116&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where there is a contract for the sale of specific goods or`
  line `where goods are subsequently appropriated to the contract, the seller may, by the terms of the contract or`
  line `appropriation, reserve the right of disposal of the goods until certain conditions are fulfilled. In such case,`
  line `notwithstanding the delivery of the goods to a buyer or to a carrier or other bailee for the purpose of`
  line `transmission to the buyer, the property in the goods does not pass to the buyer until the conditions`
  line `imposed by the seller are fulfilled.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) Where goods are shipped or delivered to a railway administration for carriage by railway and by`
  line `the bill of lading or railway receipt, as the case may be, the goods are deliverable to the order of the seller`
  line `or his agent, the seller is prima facie deemed to reserve the right of disposal.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the seller of goods draws on the buyer for the price and transmits to the buyer the bill of`
  line `exchange together with the bill of lading or, as the case may be, the railway receipt, to secure acceptance`
  line `or payment of the bill of exchange, the buyer is bound to return the bill of lading or the railway receipt if`
  line `he does not honour the bill of exchange; and, if he wrongfully retains the bill of lading or the railway`
  line `receipt, the property in the goods does not pass to him.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- In this section, the expressions "railway" and "railway administration" shall have the`
  line `meanings respectively assigned to them under the Indian Railways Act, 1890 (9 of 1890).]`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (30117)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Risk prima facie passes with property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30117&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Unless otherwise agreed, the goods remain at the`
  line `seller's risk until the property therein is transferred to the buyer, but when the property therein is`
  line `transferred to the buyer, the goods are at the buyer's risk whether delivery has been made or not:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where delivery has been delayed through the fault of either buyer or seller, the goods`
  line `are at the risk of the party in fault as regards any loss which might not have occurred but for such fault:`
  line
  line `Provided also that nothing in this section shall affect the duties or liabilities of either seller or buyer as`
  line `a bailee of the goods of the other party.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (30118)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Sale by person not the owner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30118&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act and of any other law for the`
  line `time being in force, where goods are sold by a person who is not the owner thereof and who does not sell`
  line `them under the authority or with the consent of the owner, the buyer acquires no better title to the goods`
  line `than the seller had, unless the owner of the goods is by his conduct precluded from denying the seller's`
  line `authority to sell:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where a mercantile agent is, with the consent of the owner, in possession of the goods`
  line `or of a document of title to the goods, any sale made by him, when acting in the ordinary course of`
  line `business of a mercantile agent, shall be as valid as if he were expressly authorised by the owner of the`
  line `goods to make the same; provided that the buyer acts in good faith and has not at the time of the contract`
  line `of sale notice that the seller has not authority to sell.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (30119)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Sale by one of joint owners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30119&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `If one of several joint owners of goods has the sole possession of`
  line `them by permission of the co-owners, the property in the goods is transferred to any person who buys`
  line `them of such joint owner in good faith and has not at the time of the contract of sale notice that the seller`
  line `has not authority to sell.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (30120)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Sale by person in possession under voidable contract.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30120&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `When the seller of goods has obtained`
  line `possession thereof under a contract voidable under section 19 or section 19A of the Indian Contract Act,`
  line `1872 (9 of 1872), but the contract has not been rescinded at the time of the sale, the buyer acquires a good`
  line `title to the goods, provided he buys them in good faith and without notice of the seller’s defect of title.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (30121)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Seller or buyer in possession after sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30121&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a person, having sold goods, continues or is`
  line `in possession of the goods or of the documents of title to the goods, the delivery or transfer by that person`
  line `or by a mercantile agent acting for him, of the goods or documents of title under any sale, pledge or other`
  line `disposition thereof to any person receiving the same in good faith and without notice of the previous sale`
  line `shall have the same effect as if the person making the delivery or transfer were expressly authorised by`
  line `the owner of the goods to make the same.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a person, having bought or agreed to buy goods, obtains, with the consent of the seller,`
  line `possession of the goods or the documents of title to the goods, the delivery or transfer by that person or by`
  line `a mercantile agent acting for him, of the goods or documents of title under any sale, pledge or other`
  line `disposition thereof to any person receiving the same in good faith and without notice of any lien or other`
  line `right of the original seller in respect of the goods shall have effect as if such lien or right did not exist.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (30122)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Duties of seller and buyer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30122&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `It is the duty to the seller to deliver the goods and of the buyer to`
  line `accept and pay for them, in accordance with the terms of the contract of sale.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (30123)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Payment and delivery are concurrent conditions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30123&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Unless otherwise agreed, delivery of the`
  line `goods and payment of the price are concurrent conditions, that is to say, the seller shall be ready and`
  line `willing to give possession of the goods to the buyer in exchange for the price, and the buyer shall be ready`
  line `and willing to pay the price in exchange for possession of the goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (30124)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title Delivery.
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30124&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Delivery of goods sold may be made by doing anything which the parties agree shall`
  line `be treated as delivery or which has the effect of putting the goods in the possession of the buyer or of any`
  line `person authorised to hold them on his behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (30125)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Effect of part delivery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30125&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `A delivery of part of goods, in progress of the delivery of the whole,`
  line `has the same effect, for the purpose of passing the property in such goods, as a delivery of the whole; but a delivery of part of the goods, with an intention of severing it from the whole, does not operate as a`
  line `delivery of the remainder.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (30126)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Buyer to apply for delivery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30126&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Apart from any express contract, the seller of goods is not bound`
  line `to delivery them until the buyer applies for delivery.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (30127)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Rules as to delivery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30127&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whether it is for the buyer to take possession of the goods or for the`
  line `seller to send them to the buyer is a question depending in each case on the contract, express or implied,`
  line `between the parties. Apart from any such contract, goods sold are to be delivered at the place at which`
  line `they are at the time of the sale, and goods agreed to be sold are to be delivered at the place at which they`
  line `are at the time of the agreement to sell, or, if not then in existence, at the place at which they are`
  line `manufactured or produced.`
  line
  line `(2) Where under the contract of sale the seller is bound to send the goods to the buyer, but no time`
  line `for sending them is fixed, the seller is bound to send them within a reasonable time.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the goods at the time of sale are in the possession of a third person, there is no delivery by`
  line `seller to buyer unless and until such third person acknowledges to the buyer that he holds the goods on his`
  line `behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall affect the operation of the issue or transfer of any document`
  line `of title to goods.`
  line
  line `(4) Demand or tender of delivery may be treated as ineffectual unless made at a reasonable hour.`
  line `What is a reasonable hour is a question of fact.`
  line
  line `(5) Unless otherwise agreed, the expenses of and incidental to putting the goods into a deliverable`
  line `state shall be borne by the seller.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (30128)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Delivery of wrong quantity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30128&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the seller delivers to the buyer a quantity of goods less`
  line `than he contracted to sell, the buyer may reject them, but it the buyer accepts the goods so delivered he`
  line `shall pay for them at the contract rate.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the seller delivers to the buyer a quantity of goods larger than he contracted to sell, the`
  line `buyer may accept the goods included in the contract and reject the rest, or he may reject the whole. If the`
  line `buyer accepts the whole of the goods so delivered, he shall pay for them at the contract rate.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the seller delivers to the buyer the goods he contracted to sell mixed with goods of a`
  line `different description not included in the contract, the buyer may accept the goods which are in accordance`
  line `with the contract and reject the rest, or may reject the whole.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of this section are subject to any usage of trade, special agreement or course of`
  line `dealing between the parties.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (30129)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Instalment deliveries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30129&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) Unless otherwise agreed, the buyer of goods is not bound to accept`
  line `delivery thereof by instalments.`
  line
  line `(2) Where there is a contract for the sale of goods to be delivered by stated instalments which are to`
  line `be separately paid for, and the seller makes no delivery or defective delivery in respect of one or more`
  line `instalments, or the buyer neglects or refuses to take delivery of or pay for one or more instalments, it is a`
  line `question in each case depending on the terms of the contract and the circumstances of the case, whether`
  line `the breach of contract is a repudiation of the whole contract, or whether it is a severable breach giving rise`
  line `to a claim for compensation, but not to a right to treat the whole contract as repudiated.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (30130)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Delivery to carrier or wharfinger.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30130&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, in pursuance of a contract of sale, the seller is`
  line `authorised or required to send the goods to the buyer, delivery of the goods to a carrier, whether named by`
  line `the buyer or not, for the purpose of transmission to the buyer, or delivery of the goods to a wharfinger for`
  line `safe custody, is prima facie deemed to be a delivery of the goods to the buyer.`
  line
  line `(2) Unless otherwise authorised by the buyer, the seller shall make such contract with the carrier or`
  line `wharfinger on behalf of the buyer as may be reasonable having regard to the nature of the goods and the`
  line `other circumstances of the case. If the seller omits so to do, and the goods are lost or damaged in course of transit or whilst in the custody of the wharfinger, the buyer may decline to treat the delivery to the`
  line `carrier or wharfinger as a delivery to himself, or may hold the seller responsible in damages.`
  line
  line `(3) Unless otherwise agreed, where goods are sent by the seller to the buyer by a route involving sea`
  line `transit, in curcumstances in which it is usual to insure, the seller shall give such notice to the buyer as`
  line `may enable him to insure them during their sea transit, and if the seller fails so to do, the goods shall be`
  line `deemed to be at his risk during such sea transit.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (30131)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Risk where goods are delivered at distant place.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30131&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Where the seller of goods agrees to deliver`
  line `them at his own risk at a place other than that where they are when sold, the buyer shall, nevertheless,`
  line `unless otherwise agreed, take any risk of deterioration in the goods necessarily incident to the course of`
  line transit.
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (30132)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Buyer’s right of examining the goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30132&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where goods are delivered to the buyer which he`
  line `has not previously examined, he is not deemed to have accepted them unless and until he has had a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of examining them for the purpose of ascertaining whether they are in conformity`
  line `with the contract.`
  line
  line `(2) Unless otherwise agreed, when the seller tenders delivery of goods to the buyer, he is bound, on`
  line `request, to afford the buyer a reasonable opportunity of examining the goods for the purpose of`
  line `ascertaining whether they are in conformity with the contract.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (30133)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title Acceptance.
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30133&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `The buyer is deemed to have accepted the goods when he intimates to the seller`
  line `that he has accepted them, or when the goods have been delivered to him and he does any act in relation`
  line `to them which is inconsistent with the ownership of the seller, or when, after the lapse of a reasonable`
  line `time, he retains the goods without intimating to the seller that he has rejected them.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (30134)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Buyer not bound to return rejected goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30134&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `Unless otherwise agreed, where goods are`
  line `delivered to the buyer and he refuses to accept them, having the right so to do, he is not bound to return`
  line `them to the seller, but it is sufficient if he intimates to the seller that he refuses to accept them.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (30135)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Liability of buyer for neglecting or refusing delivery of goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30135&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `When the seller is ready and`
  line `willing to deliver the goods and requests the buyer to take delivery, and the buyer does not within a`
  line `reasonable time after such request take delivery of the goods, he is liable to the seller for any loss`
  line `occasioned by his neglect or refusal to take delivery, and also for a reasonable charge for the care and`
  line `custody of the goods:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall affect the rights of the seller where the neglect or refusal of`
  line `the buyer to take delivery amounts to a repudiation of the contract.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (30136)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `“Unpaid seller” defined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30136&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) The seller of goods is deemed to be an "unpaid seller" within the`
  line `meaning of this Act—`
  line
  line `(a) when the whole of the price has not been paid or tendered;`
  line
  line `(b) when a bill of exchange or other negotiable instrument has been received as conditional`
  line `payment, and the condition on which it was received has not been fulfilled by reason of the dishonour`
  line `of the instrument or otherwise.`
  line
  line `(2) In this Chapter, the term "seller" includes any person who is in the position of a seller, as, for`
  line `instance, an agent of the seller to whom the bill of lading has been endorsed, or a consignor or agent who`
  line `has himself paid, or is directly responsible for, the price.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (30137)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Unpaid seller’s rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30137&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and of any law for the time`
  line `being in force, notwithstanding that the property in the goods may have passed to the buyer, the unpaid`
  line `seller of goods, as such, has by implication of law—`
  line
  line `(a) a lien on the goods for the price while he is in possession of them;`
  line
  line `(b) in case of the insolvency of the buyer a right of stopping the goods in transit after he has`
  line `parted with the possession of them;`
  line
  line `(c) a right of re-sale as limited by this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the property in goods has not passed to the buyer, the unpaid seller has, in addition to his`
  line `other remedies, a right of withholding delivery similar to and co-extensive with his rights of lien and`
  line `stoppage in transit where the property has passed to the buyer.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (30138)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Seller’s lien.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30138&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the unpaid seller of goods who is in`
  line `possession of them is entitled to retain possession of them until payment or tender of the price in the`
  line `following cases, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) where the goods have been sold without any stipulation as to credit;`
  line
  line `(b) where the goods have been sold on credit, but the term of credit has expired;`
  line
  line `(c) where the buyer becomes insolvent.`
  line
  line `(2) The seller may exercise his right of lien notwithstanding that he is in possession of the goods as`
  line `agent or bailee for the buyer.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (30139)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Part delivery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30139&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `Where an unpaid seller has made part delivery of the goods, he may exercise his`
  line `right of lien on the remainder, unless such part delivery has been made under such circumstances as to`
  line `show an agreement to waive the lien.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (30140)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Termination of lien.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30140&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) The unpaid seller of goods loses his lien thereon—`
  line
  line `(a) when he delivers the goods to a carrier or other bailee for the purpose of transmission to the`
  line `buyer without reserving the right of disposal of the goods;`
  line
  line `(b) when the buyer or his agent lawfully obtains possession of the goods;`
  line
  line `(c) by waiver thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) The unpaid seller of goods, having a lien thereon, does not lose his lien by reason only that he has`
  line `obtained a decree for the price of the goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (30141)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Right of stoppage in transit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30141&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, when the buyer of goods`
  line `becomes insolvent, the unpaid seller who has parted with the possession of the goods has the right of`
  line `stopping them in transit, that is to say, he may resume possession of the goods as long as they are in the`
  line `course of transit, and may retain them until payment or tender of the price.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (30142)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Duration of transit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30142&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) Goods are deemed to be in course of transit from the time when they`
  line `are delivered to a carrier or other bailee for the purpose of transmission to the buyer, until the buyer or his`
  line `agent in that behalf takes delivery of them from such carrier or other bailee.`
  line
  line `(2) If the buyer or his agent in that behalf obtains delivery of the goods before their arrival at the`
  line `appointed destination, the transit is at an end.`
  line
  line `(3) If, after the arrival of the goods at the appointed destination, the carrier or other bailee`
  line `acknowledges to the buyer or his agent that he holds the goods on his behalf and continues in possession`
  line `of them as bailee for the buyer or his agent, the transit is at an end and it is immaterial that a further`
  line `destination for the goods may have been indicated by the buyer.`
  line
  line `(4) If the goods are rejected by the buyer and the carrier or other bailee continues in possession of`
  line `them, the transit is not deemed to be at an end, even if the seller has refused to receive them back.`
  line
  line `(5) When goods are delivered to a ship chartered by the buyer, it is a question depending on the`
  line `circumstances of the particular case, whether they are in the possession of the master as a carrier or as`
  line `agent of the buyer.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the carrier or other bailee wrongfully refuses to deliver the goods to the buyer or his agent`
  line `in that behalf, the transit is deemed to be at an end.`
  line
  line `(7) Where part delivery of the goods has been made to the buyer or his agent in that behalf, the`
  line `remainder of the goods may be stopped in transit, unless such part delivery has been given in such`
  line `circumstances as to show an agreement to give up possession of the whole of the goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (30143)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `How stoppage in transit is effected.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30143&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) The unpaid sellermay exercise his right of stoppage in`
  line `transit either by taking actual possession of the goods, or by giving notice of his claim to the carrier or`
  line `other bailee in whose possession the goods are. Such notice may be given either to the person in actual`
  line `possession of the goods or to his principal. In the latter case the notice, to be effectual, shall be given at`
  line `such time and in such circumstances that the principal, by the exercise of reasonable diligence, may`
  line `communicate it to his servant or agent in time to prevent a delivery to the buyer.`
  line
  line `(2) When notice of stoppage in transit is given by the seller to the carrier or other bailee in possession`
  line `of the goods, he shall re-deliver the goods to, or according to the directions of, the seller. The expenses of`
  line `such re-delivery shall be borne by the seller.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (30144)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Effect of sub-sale or pledge by buyer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30144&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the unpaid`
  line `seller's right of lien or stoppage in transit is not affected by any sale or other disposition of the goods`
  line `which the buyer may have made, unless the seller has assented thereto:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a document of title to goods has been issued or lawfully transferred to any person`
  line `as buyer or owner of the goods, and that person transfers the document to a person who takes the`
  line `document in good faith and for consideration, then, if such last mentioned transfer was by way a sale, the`
  line `unpaid sellers right of lien or stoppage in transit is defeated, and, if such last mentioned transfer was by`
  line `way of pledge or other disposition for value, the unpaid sellers right of lien or stoppage is transit can`
  line `only be exercised subject to the rights of the transferee.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the transfer is by way of pledge, the unpaid seller may require the pledgee to have the`
  line `amount secured by the pledge satisfied in the first instance, as far as possible, out of any other goods or`
  line `securities of the buyer in the hands of the pledgee and available against the buyer.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (30145)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Sale not generally rescinded by lien or stoppage in transit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30145&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of`
  line `this section, a contract of sale is not rescinded by the mere exercise by an unpaid seller of his right of lien`
  line `or stoppage in transit.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the goods are of a perishable nature, or where the unpaid seller who has exercised his right`
  line `of lien or stoppage in transit gives notice to the buyer of his intention to re-sell, the unpaid seller may, if`
  line `the buyer does not within a reasonable time pay or tender the price, re-sell the goods within a reasonable`
  line `time and recover from the original buyer damages for any loss occasioned by his breach of contract, but`
  line `the buyer shall not be entitled to any profit which may occur on the re-sale. If such notice is not given, the`
  line `unpaid seller shall not be entitled to recover such damages and the buyer shall be entitled to the profit, if`
  line `any, on the re-sale.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an unpaid seller who has exercised his right of lien or stoppage in transit re-sells the goods,`
  line `the buyer acquires a good title thereto as against the original buyer, notwithstanding that no notice of the`
  line `re-sale has been given to the original buyer.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the seller expressly reserves a right of re-sale in case the buyer should make default, and,`
  line `on the buyer making default, re-sells the goods, the original contract of sale is thereby rescinded, but`
  line `without prejudice to any claim which the seller may have for damages.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (30146)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Suit for price.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30146&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where under a contract of sale the property in the goods has passed to the`
  line `buyer and the buyer wrongfully neglects or refuses to pay for the goods according to the terms of the`
  line `contract, the seller may sue him for the price of the goods.`
  line
  line `(2) Where under a contract of sale the price is payable on a day certain irrespective of delivery and`
  line `the buyer wrongfully neglects or refuses to pay such pirce, the seller may sue him for the price although`
  line `the property in the goods has not passed and the goods have not been appropriated to the contract.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (30147)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Damages for non-acceptance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30147&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `Where the buyer wrongfully neglects or refuses to accept and`
  line `pay for the goods, the seller may sue him for damages for non-acceptance.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (30148)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Damages for non-delivery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30148&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `Where the seller wrongfully neglects or refuses to deliver the`
  line `goods to the buyer, the buyer may sue the seller for damages for non-delivery.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (30149)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Specific performance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30149&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of Chapter II of the Specific Relief Act, 1877`
  line `(1 of 1877), in any suit for breach of contract to deliver specific or ascertained goods, the Court may, if it`
  line `thinks fit, on the application of the plaintiff, by its decree direct that the contract shall be performed`
  line `specifically, without giving the defendant the option of retaining the goods on payment of damages. The`
  line `decree may be unconditional, or upon such terms and conditions as to damages, payment of the price or`
  line `otherwise, as the Court may deem just, and the application of the plaintiff may be made at any time before`
  line `the decree.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (30150)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Remedy for breach of warranty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30150&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where there is a breach of warranty by file seller, or`
  line `where the buyer elects or is compelled to treat any breach of a condition on the part of the seller as a`
  line `breach of warranty, the buyer is not by reason only of such breach of warranty entitled to reject the goods;`
  line `but he may—`
  line
  line `(a) set up against the seller the breach of warranty in diminution or extinction of the price; or`
  line
  line `(b) sue the seller for damages for breach of warranty.`
  line
  line `(2) The fact that a buyer has set up a breach of warranty in diminution or extinction of the price does`
  line `not prevent him from suing for the same breach of warranty if he has suffered further damage.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (30151)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Repudiation of contract before due date.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30151&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `Where either party to a contract of sale repudiates`
  line `the contract before the date of delivery, the other may either treat the contract as subsisting and wait till`
  line `the date of delivery, or he may treat the contract as rescinded and sue for damages for the breach.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (30152)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Interest by way of damages and special damages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30152&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in this Act shall affect the right`
  line `of the seller or the buyer to recover interest or special damages in any case where by law interest or`
  line `special damages may be recoverable, or to recover the money paid where the consideration for the`
  line `payment of it has failed.`
  line
  line `(2) In the absence of a contract to the contrary, the Court may award interest at such rate as it thinks`
  line `fit on the amount of the price—`
  line
  line `(a) to the seller in a suit by him for the amount of the price— from the date of the tender of the`
  line `goods or from the date on which the price was payable;`
  line
  line `(b) to the buyer in a suit by him for the refund of the price in a case of a breach of the contract on`
  line `the part of the seller—from the date on which the payment was made.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (30153)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Exclusion of implied terms and conditions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30153&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `Where any right, duty or liability would arise`
  line `under a contract of sale by implication of law, it may be negatived or varied by express agreement or by`
  line `the course of dealing between the parties, or by usage, if the usage is such as to bind both parties to the`
  line contract.
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (30154)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Reasonable time a question of fact.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30154&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `Where in this Act any reference is made to a reasonable`
  line `time, the question what is a reasonable time is a question of fact.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (30155)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Auction sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30155&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `In the case of a sale by auction`
  line
  line `(1) Where goods are put up for sale in lots, each lot is prima facie deemed to be the subject of a`
  line `separate contract of sale;`
  line
  line `(2) the sale is complete when the auctioneer announces its completion by the fall of the hammer`
  line `or in other customary manner; and, until such announcement is made, any bidder may retract his bid;`
  line
  line `(3) a right to bid may be reserved expressely by or on behalf of the seller and, where such right is`
  line `expressly so reserved, but not otherwise, the seller or any one person on his behalf may, subject to the`
  line `provisions hereinafter contained, bid at the auction;`
  line
  line `(4) where the sale is not notified to be subject to a right to bid on behalf of the seller, it shall not`
  line `be lawful for the seller to bid himself or to employ any person to bid at such sale, or for the auctioneer`
  line `knowingly to take any bid from the seller or any such person; and any sale contravening this rule may`
  line `be treated as fraudulent by the buyer;`
  line
  line `(5) the sale may be notified to be subject to a reserved or upset, price;`
  line
  line `(6) if the seller makes use of pretended bidding to raise the price, the sale is voidable at the option`
  line `of the buyer.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64_a:
  sectionId (30156)
  sectionNo 64A
  orderNo 65
  title `In contracts of sale, amount of increased or decreased taxes to be added or deducted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 1963, s. 5, for section 64A (w.e.f. 22-9-1963). Earlier it was inserted by Act 41 of 1940, s 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30156&sectionno=64A&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_64_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[64A. In contracts of sale, amount of increased or decreased taxes to be added or deducted.—(1) Unless a different intention appears from the terms of the contract, in the event of any tax of the nature`
  line `described in sub-section (2) being imposed, increased, decreased or remitted in respect of any goods after`
  line `the making of any contract for the sale or purchase of such goods without stipulation as to the payment of`
  line `tax where tax was not chargeable at the time of the making of the contract, or for the sale or purchase of`
  line `such goods tax-paid where tax was chargeable at that time,—`
  line
  line `(a) if such imposition or increase so takes effect that the tax or increased tax, as the case may be,`
  line `or any part of such tax is paid or is payable, the seller may add so much to the contract price as will`
  line `be equivalent to the amount paid or payable in respect of such tax or increase of tax, and he shall be`
  line `entitled to be paid and to sue for and recover such addition; and`
  line
  line `(b) if such decrease or remission so takes effect that the decreased tax only, or no tax, as the case`
  line `may be, is paid or is payable, the buyer may deduct so much from the contract price as will be`
  line `equivalent to the decrease of tax or remitted tax, and he shall not be liable to pay, or be sued for, or in`
  line `respect of, such deduction.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) apply to the following taxes, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) any duty of customs or excise on goods;`
  line
  line `(b) any tax on the sale or purchase of goods.]`
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (30157)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 66
  title [Repealed.].
  content `[Repeal.] --Rep. by the Repealing Act, 1938 (1 of 1938), s. 2 nd Sch.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30157&sectionno=65&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (30158)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 67
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738&sectionId=30158&sectionno=66&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00059_193003_1523350185738
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in this Act or in any repeal effected thereby shall affect or be deemed to`
  line affect—
  line
  line `(a) any right, title, interest, obligation or liability already acquired, accrued or incurred before the`
  line `commencement of this Act, or`
  line
  line `(b) any legal proceedings or remedy in respect of any such right, title, interest, obligation or`
  line `liability, or`
  line
  line `(c) anything done or suffered before the commencement of this Act, or`
  line
  line `(d) any enactment relating to the sale of goods which is not expressly repealed by this Act, or`
  line
  line `(e) any rule of law not inconsistent with this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The rules of insolvency relating to contracts for the sale of goods shall continue to apply thereto,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of this Act relating to contracts of sale do not apply to any transaction in the form`
  line `of a contract of sale which is intended to operate by way of mortgage, pledge, charge or other security.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
